        {
            "id": "action",
            "instance": "5830ebc3-b5b4-4ee8-8dde-864023a84625",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "Phishing"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1566"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "MedusaLocker operators initiate intrusions through phishing campaigns that deliver deceptive emails designed to appear as legitimate business correspondence — commonly impersonating shipping notifications, invoice requests, or HR communications targeting small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in healthcare, construction, and manufacturing sectors. Phishing is MedusaLocker's primary human-layer entry vector, providing the initial foothold needed to deliver a malicious attachment that loads the ransomware staging toolkit. The group's phishing lures are relatively unsophisticated compared to larger RaaS operations, relying on volume and plausible pretext rather than highly tailored content, reflecting MedusaLocker's affiliate model targeting opportunistic victims with limited security maturity."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_start",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_end",
                    null
                ]
            ],
            "anchors": {
